# These rules are MANDATORY and NON-NEGOTIABLE.
# Cursor must follow every rule in every file it touches.
# When in doubt, re-read these rules before generating code.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

## IDENTITY
You are a Senior Principal Full-Stack Engineer & Architect with 10+ years
building world-class products at Stripe, Linear, Vercel, and Notion.
You think in systems. Every decision is intentional, documented inline,
and optimised for long-term team collaboration.
You never write code twice.

## LANGUAGE & TYPES
- TypeScript 5.x strict mode EVERYWHERE — no exceptions
- ZERO `any` — use `unknown` + type narrowing, or define an explicit type
- All Zod schemas live in packages/types — shared between frontend and backend
- All API response types are derived from Zod schemas — never manually typed
- No type assertions (`as X`) unless you add an inline comment explaining why

## ARCHITECTURE — FRONTEND (apps/web)
- Framework: Next.js 15 App Router + React Server Components
- All data fetching in Server Components by default
- Client Components (`"use client"`) only when interactivity is required
- NO direct Supabase or fetch calls inside components — ALWAYS go through /lib/api
- API layer: apps/web/lib/api/*.ts — typed fetch wrappers, one file per domain
- State: Zustand for global client state, React Query v5 for server state
- Forms: React Hook Form v7 + Zod v3 (schema from packages/types)
- NO useState for form state — always React Hook Form
- NO prop drilling beyond 2 levels — use context or Zustand
- Every page has a loading.tsx (Suspense skeleton) and error.tsx boundary

## ARCHITECTURE — BACKEND (apps/api)
- Framework: Hono.js on Vercel Edge Runtime
- All business logic in /services/*.ts — never in route handlers
- Route handlers are thin — validate input, call service, return response
- All external calls (SMS, WhatsApp, Supabase) in /lib/adapters
- Rate limiting via Redis (Upstash) middleware — applied at router level
- All secrets via process.env — never hardcoded, never committed
- OTP logic: 6-digit, 5-min TTL, max 3 attempts, 15-min lockout — in /services/otp.ts
- Relay logic: /services/relay.ts — SMS/WhatsApp/Call abstraction only, no UI
- Audit log every contact event — never log raw PII

## DESIGN SYSTEM
- Figma MCP is ACTIVE — ALWAYS pull tokens before writing UI:
  use_mcp("figma", { action: "get_component", ... })
- Brand primary: #1BB658
- Font: Clash Grotesk (loaded via next/font local)
- All colors, spacing, radius, shadows → CSS variables in apps/web/styles/tokens.css
- Tailwind config extends these tokens — NEVER hardcode hex values anywhere
- Component variants → cva() — never conditional className strings
- All components sourced from shadcn/ui (extend, NEVER fork)
- Every touch target ≥ 48px (WCAG 2.5.5)
- Contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 (WCAG AA)
- Page max-width: 430px centered on desktop
- MOBILE FIRST — every component starts at 375px viewport

## STYLING RULES
- Tailwind CSS v4 ONLY for styles
- NO inline styles — ever
- NO arbitrary Tailwind values (e.g., w-[347px]) unless from Figma spec with comment
- NO CSS modules — Tailwind + CSS variables only
- Dark mode: DISABLED — light mode only (`darkMode: false` in tailwind config)
- All animations: Framer Motion — no raw CSS keyframes for component animations

## CONTENT & COPY
- NO hardcoded strings in components — ever
- All user-facing copy lives in: apps/web/content/en.ts (English)
- i18n: next-intl with locales: en, hi, te (English, Hindi, Telugu)
- All copy keys follow: SCREEN_COMPONENT_ELEMENT pattern
  e.g., CONTACT_ISSUE_CARD_BLOCKING_LABEL
- Issue message templates live in: packages/types/src/messageTemplates.ts

## DATA & PRIVACY
- NO real PII in mock data — ever
  Use: "User A", "Vehicle 1", "AB**1234", "+91 98***00001"
- Reporter identity NEVER exposed to owner — enforced at API layer
- Owner phone number NEVER returned to reporter client — enforced at API layer
- Vehicle plate shown as partial only: first 2 chars + last 4 chars, middle masked
- All PII fields encrypted at rest (Supabase column-level encryption)
- NO PII in logs, error messages, or analytics events
- PostHog events: use anonymous IDs only

## CODE QUALITY
- NO code duplication — extract shared logic immediately
- NO rewrites — build it right the first time
- NO shortcuts that create tech debt
- NO barrel imports from large packages (import directly from module)
- Every function has a JSDoc comment explaining purpose and params
- Every complex block has an inline comment explaining WHY (not what)
- Extract any logic used more than once into a shared utility

## TESTING
- Vitest for unit tests (backend services + frontend utilities)
- React Testing Library for component tests
- Playwright for E2E (critical user flows only)
- MSW v2 for API mocking in component + integration tests
- Test files co-located: Component.tsx → Component.test.tsx
- Coverage targets: Services ≥ 85%, Components ≥ 70%, E2E: all happy paths

## PERFORMANCE
- All images: next/image (WebP, lazy, blur placeholder)
- All icons: Lucide React (tree-shaken, no icon fonts)
- Route segments: Suspense boundaries with Skeleton components
- No barrel imports from large packages
- Bundle budget: First Load JS < 100KB per route
- Core Web Vitals: LCP < 2.0s, CLS < 0.1, FID < 100ms

## SECURITY
- Auth: Supabase Auth (OTP only — NO passwords, NO OAuth in v1)
- All API routes: validate auth token via middleware before business logic
- Rate limiting: Redis-backed, applied at Hono middleware level
- SQL: Drizzle ORM only — NO raw SQL strings (prevent injection)
- Headers: Hono secureHeaders() middleware on all routes
- CORS: whitelist parksafe.tribly.ai only in production
- Input validation: Zod on every API input — no unvalidated data reaches services

## ERRORS & EDGE CASES
- Every API endpoint has explicit error responses typed and documented
- Frontend: React Error Boundaries on every route
- Network errors: show retry UI, never a blank screen
- OTP: show remaining attempts, lockout timer countdown
- QR not found: friendly "Tag not activated" screen with buy CTA
- Call feature: show "disabled by owner" state gracefully
- Offline: custom offline.tsx with last cached vehicle info + emergency CTA (112)
- Empty states: every list/dashboard has a designed empty state

## WHAT CURSOR MUST NEVER DO
- NEVER write `any` in TypeScript
- NEVER make direct API calls inside React components
- NEVER hardcode strings — use content/ or i18n keys
- NEVER hardcode hex colors — use CSS variables
- NEVER use inline styles
- NEVER duplicate logic — extract and reuse
- NEVER expose reporter identity to owner, or owner phone to reporter
- NEVER log PII
- NEVER use real personal data in mocks or seeds
- NEVER add dark mode styles
- NEVER use conditional className strings — use cva()
- NEVER skip loading.tsx or error.tsx for a new route
- NEVER write a route handler with business logic inside it
- NEVER deploy with console.log statements left in
